g.text: Lets Understand IAS by an example.
Suppose lets take ecample of flipkart, They want 400 servers for thier application to run smooth,
now either they can have there own on premises server or use Cloud providers like AWS, Azure, GCP etc.
But nowadays in industry they prefer multi-cloud approach, like following.
Now as an DevOps Engg you took decision to use AWS for your 400 servers, and this Decision of yours
So you used AWS automation using AWS CFT(Cloud Formation Templates).
You wrote 100s of CFT Scripts to automate the creation of EC2 instances, S3 Buckets etc.
But now after 4 months you decide to migrate to GCP because AWS was not that Cheap for your organization.
so now what you need to do is to migrate all the scripts you wrote to automate the creation of resources
But, now you have to learn about writing scripts for GCP, and this is not an effiecent way for DevOps Engg.
But this is not the main problem, Now a days People use "Multi-Cloud" technique for optimal performance
Since you are using Multi-Cloud technique You again have to learn and write different scripts according to
the Cloud Platform you choose, and this is not and Efficent way, so thier need an tool to solve this problem related
So to solve this Problem a Tool came named "Terraform", which is developed by HashiCorp.
This tool works on the Principle of "API as Code".
Terraform, says that write Terraform scripts, and inside that script just mention which cloud provider
you wish to use, and rest assured terraform will take care of.
- Terraform says that if you want to migrate from one Provider to another, You have to make bare minimum changes
into your script, Like There is script called, "Providers" in that we provide all the information related to the Cloud
- Terraform uses a concept of API as Code, using which it calls the APIs Exposed by the Cloud Providers, to create
